You O
have O
undefined O
behavior O
in O
your O
code O
: O
You O
haven O
an O
uninitialized O
pointer O
input O
in O
getinput O
. O

Uninitialized O
( O
non-static B-Data_Type
) O
local O
variables O
have O
an O
indeterminate O
value O
, O
and O
it O
will O
seem O
to O
be O
random O
. O

As O
the O
value O
is O
indeterminate O
( O
and O
seemingly O
random O
) O
the O
scanf O
call O
will O
write O
to O
some O
unknown O
place O
in O
memory O
, O
overwriting O
whatever O
was O
there O
. O

You O
could O

solve O
this O
by O
making O
input O
an O
array B-Data_Structure
. O

OP_BLOCK O
: O
( O
output O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

actually O
super() O
is O
not O
syntactic O
sugar O
, O
its O
purpose O
is O
to O
invoke O
parent O
implementation O
of O
a O
certain O
method O
. O

You O
have O
to O
use O
super() O
when O
you O
want O
to O
override O
a O
parent O
method O
, O
you O
do O
n't O
have O
to O
use O
super() O
when O
instead O
you O
want O
to O
overwrite O
a O
method O
. O

The O
difference O
is O
that O
in O
the O
first O
case O
you O
want O
to O
add O
extra O
behavior O
( O
aka O
code O
execution O
) O
before O
or O
after O
the O
original O
implementation O
, O
in O
the O
second O
you O
want O
a O
completely O
different O
implementation O
. O

You O
ca O
n't O
use O
self.method_name() O
in O
an O
override O
, O
the O
result O
will O
be O
a O
recursion O
error O
! O

( O
RuntimeError O
: O
maximum O
recursion O
depth O
exceeded O
) O

Example O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_4468 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

Given O
a O
base O
class O
A O
, O
with O
a O
method O
m O
, O
B O
extends O
A O
by O
overriding O
m O
, O
C O
extends O
A O
by O
overwriting O
m O
, O
and O
D O
generates O
an O
error O
! O

EDIT O
: O

I O
just O
realized O
that O
you O
actually O
have O
2 O
different O
methods O
( O
test_a O
and O
test_b O
) O
. O

My O
answer O
is O
still O
valid O
, O
but O
regarding O
your O
specific O
scenario O
: O

you O
should O
use O
self.test_a() O
unless O
you O
override/overwrite O
that O
method O
in O
your O
class O
B O
and O
you O
want O
to O
execute O
the O
original O
implementation. O
. O
so O
we O
can O
say O
that O
calling O
super().test_a() O
or O
self.test_a() O
it O
's O
the O
same O
given O
that O
you O
'll O
never O
override/overwrite O
the O
original O
test_a() O
in O
your O
subclasses. O
. O
however O
is O
a O
nonsense O
to O
use O
super() O
if O
not O
for O
an O
override/overwrite O

will O

to O

. O

, O

, O

. O

The O
Haskell B-Programming_Language
type O
system O
has O
a O
number O
of O
features O
which O
all O
exist O
in O
other O
languages O
, O
but O
are O
rarely O
combined O
within O
a O
single O
, O
consistent O
language O
: O

it O
is O
a O
sound O
, O
static B-Data_Type
type O
system O
, O
meaning O
that O
a O
number O
of O
errors O
are O
guaranteed O
not O
to O
happen O
at O
runtime O
without O
needing O
runtime O
type O
checks O
( O
this O
is O
also O
the O
case O
in O
Caml B-Programming_Language
, O
SML B-Programming_Language
and O
almost O
the O
case O
in O
Java B-Programming_Language
, O
but O
not O
in O
, O
say O
, O
Lisp B-Programming_Language
, O
Python B-Programming_Language
, O
C B-Programming_Language
, O
or O
C++ B-Programming_Language
) O
; O

it O
peforms O
static B-Data_Type
type O
reconstruction O
, O
meaning O
that O
the O
programmer O
does O
n't O
need O
to O
write O
types O
unless O
he O
wants O
to O
, O
the O
compiler B-Application
will O
reconstruct O
them O
on O
its O
own O
( O
this O
is O
also O
the O
case O
in O
Caml B-Programming_Language
and O
SML B-Programming_Language
, O
but O
not O
in O
Java B-Programming_Language
or O
C B-Programming_Language
) O
; O

it O
supports O
impredicative O
polymorphism O
( O
type O
variables O
) O
, O
even O
at O
higher O
kinds O
( O
unlike O
Caml B-Programming_Language
and O
SML B-Programming_Language
, O
or O
any O
other O
production-ready O
language O
known O
to O
me O
) O
; O

it O
has O
good O
support O
for O
overloading O
( O
type O
classes O
) O
( O
unlike O
Caml B-Programming_Language
and O
SML B-Programming_Language
) O
. O

Whether O
any O
of O
those O
make O
Haskell B-Programming_Language
a O
better O
language O
is O
open O
to O
discussion O
— O
for O
example O
, O
while O
I O
happen O
to O
like O
type O
classes O
a O
lot O
, O
I O
know O
quite O
a O
few O
Caml B-Programming_Language
programmers O
who O
strongly O
dislike O
overloading O
and O
prefer O
to O
use O
the O
module O
system O
. O

On O
the O
other O
hand O
, O
the O
Haskell B-Programming_Language
type O
system O
lacks O
a O
few O
features O
that O
other O
languages O
support O
elegantly O
: O

it O
has O
no O
support O
for O
runtime O
dispatch O
( O
unlike O
Java B-Programming_Language
, O
Lisp B-Programming_Language
, O
and O
Julia B-Programming_Language
) O
; O

it O
has O
no O
support O
for O
existential O
types O
and O
GADTs O
( O
these O
are O
both O
GHC O
extensions O
) O
; O

it O
has O
no O
support O
for O
dependent O
types O
( O
unlike O
Coq B-Programming_Language
, O
Agda B-Programming_Language
and O
Idris B-Programming_Language
) O
. O

Again O
, O
whether O
any O
of O
these O
are O
desirable O
features O
in O
a O
general-purpose O
programming O
language O
is O
open O
to O
discussion O
. O

One O
major O
difference O
between O
Haskell B-Programming_Language
's O
type O
system O
and O
that O
of O
most O
OO O
languages O
is O
that O
the O
ability O
for O
a O
function O
to O
have O
side O
effects O
is O
represented O
by O
a O
data O
type O
( O
a O
monad B-Data_Type
such O
as O
IO B-Data_Type
) O
. O

This O
allows O
you O
to O
write O
pure O
functions O
that O
the O
compiler B-Application
can O
verify O
are O
side-effect-free O
and O
referentially O
transparent O
, O
which O
generally O
means O
that O
they O
're O
easier O
to O
understand O
and O
less O
prone O
to O
bugs O
. O

It O
's O
possible O
to O
write O
side-effect-free O
code O
in O
other O
languages O
, O
but O
you O
do O
n't O
have O
the O
compiler B-Application
's O
help O
in O
doing O
so O
. O

Haskell B-Programming_Language
makes O
you O
think O
more O
carefully O
about O
which O
parts O
of O
your O
program O
need O
to O
have O
side O
effects O
( O
such O
as O
I/O B-Data_Type
or O
mutable B-Data_Type
variables O
) O
and O
which O
parts O
should O
be O
pure O
. O

Also O
, O
although O
it O
's O
not O
quite O
part O
of O
the O
type O
system O
itself O
, O
the O
fact O
that O
function O
definitions O
in O
Haskell B-Programming_Language
are O
expressions O
( O
rather O
than O
lists O
of O
statements O
) O
means O
that O
more O
of O
the O
code O
is O
subject O
to O
type-checking O
. O

In O
languages O
like O
C++ B-Programming_Language
and O
Java B-Programming_Language
, O
it O
's O
often O
possible O
to O
introduce O
logic O
errors O
by O
writing O
statements O
in O
the O
wrong O
order O
, O
since O
the O
compiler B-Application
does O
n't O
have O
a O
way O
to O
determine O
that O
one O
statement O
must O
precede O
another O
. O

For O
example O
, O
you O
might O
have O
one O
line O
that O
modifies O
an O
object O
's O
state O
, O
and O
another O
line O
that O
does O
something O
important O
based O
on O
that O
state O
, O
and O
it O
's O
up O
to O
you O
to O
ensure O
that O
these O
things O
happen O
in O
the O
correct O
order O
. O

In O
Haskell B-Programming_Language
, O
this O
kind O
of O
ordering O
dependency O
tends O
to O
be O
expressed O
through O
function O
composition O
— O
e.g O
. O
f O
( O
g O
x O
) O
means O
that O
g O
must O
run O
first O
— O
and O
the O
compiler B-Application
can O
check O
the O
return O
type O
of O
g O
against O
the O
argument O
type O
of O
f O
to O
make O
sure O
you O
have O
n't O
composed O
them O
the O
wrong O
way O
. O

keys() O
does O
n't O
return O
a O
Set B-Library_Class
, O
it O
returns O
an O
Enumeration<K> O
. O

Hashtable B-Library_Class
is O
a O
very O
legacy O
class O
no O
longer O
recommended O
for O
use O
. O

It O
is O
replaced O
by O
HashMap B-Library_Class
, O
or O
ConcurrentHashMap B-Library_Class
† O
. O

It O
existed O
before O
the O
JCF B-Library
did O
, O
therefore O
the O
standard O
way O
to O
get O
to O
the O
keys B-Library_Class
at O
the O
start O
was O
through O
an O
Enumeration B-Library_Class
- O
the O
original O
Java B-Programming_Language
interface O
for O
moving O
through O
a O
collection O
of O
objects O
. O

Then O
came O
Java B-Programming_Language
1.2 O
, O
and O
the O
JCF B-Library
. O

Hashtable B-Library_Class
was O
retrofitted O
for O
the O
Map O
interface O
with O
the O
keySet() O
method O
that O
returned O
a O
Set B-Library_Class
( O
also O
introduced O
with O
the O
JCF B-Library
) O
. O

The O
keys O
method O
was O
retained O
for O
legacy O
compatibility O
reasons O
. O

The O
Set B-Library_Class
returned O
from O
the O
new O
method O
achieves O
two O
things O
: O

conveys O
intent O
- O
it O
reinforces O
the O
fact O
that O
the O
keys O
of O
a O
Hashtable B-Library_Class
are O
a O
mathematical O
set O

implements O
Iterable B-Library_Class
<T>, I-Library_Class
which O
replaces O
Enumerable<T> B-Library_Class

† O
From O
the O
Hashtable B-Library_Class
documentation I-Library_Class
: O

OP_BLOCK O
: O
( O
output O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

This O
has O
probably O
been O
answered O
elsewhere O
, O
but O

. O

By O
default O
AWS B-Application
refuses O
non-POST O
requests O
. O

Specifically O
it O
has O
code O
in O
action_controller_dispatcher.rb O
that O
reads O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_423 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

Basically O
you O
have O
to O
either O
set O
up O
the O
request O
to O
POST O
the O
request O
instead O
of O
GETting O
it O
. O

Or O
you O
have O
to O
override O
AWS B-Application
's O
handling O
of O
GET O
requests O
. O

( O
You O
might O
try O
editing O
the O
code O
inside O
the O
gem O
, O
but O
( O
1) O
that O
will O
get O
overwritten O
when O
you O
update O
the O
gem O
and O
( O
2) O
I O
'm O
not O
sure O
how O
good O
an O
idea O
that O
is O
in O
general O
and O
( O
3) O
I O
've O
never O
tried O
it O
. O

The O
former O
is O
likely O
more O
appropriate O
if O
you O
have O
control O
of O
the O
code O
generating O
the O
request O
. O

If O
you O
do O
n't O
, O
Zack O
Chandler O
had O
a O
workaround O
( O
for O
QuickBooks B-Application
's O
connection O
to O
a O
web-service O
, O
but O
it O
should O
work O
in O
any O
case O
) O
, O
here O
. O

I O
'm O
quoting O
it O
below O
in O
case O
the O
url O
changes O
. O

OP_BLOCK O
: O
( O
output O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

Obviously O
the O
code O

Yes O
, O
no O
problem O
with O
this O
! O

The O
number O
of O
shards B-Library_Class
does O
n't O
limit O
the O
number O
of O
consumers B-Library_Class
a O
stream B-Library_Class
can O
have O
. O

In O
you O
case O
, O
it O
will O
just O
limit O
the O
number O
of O
concurrent O
invocations O
of O
each O
lambda O
. O

This O
means O
that O
for O
each O
consumers B-Library_Class
, O
you O
can O
only O
have O
the O
number O
of O
shards B-Library_Class
of O
concurrent O
executions O
. O

Seethis O
doc O
for O
more O
details O
. O

There O
are O
several O
options O
to O
achieve O
schema O
flexibility O
in O
an O
( O
SQL B-Programming_Language
- O
) O
RDBMS B-Application
: O

1 O
. O
use O
a O
Entity O
– O
attribute O
– O
value O
model O

2 O
. O
store O
a O
JSON O
document O

Depending O
on O
your O
use O
case O
, O
data O
volume O
etc O
. O

a O
nosql B-Application
db O
could O
be O
the O
better O
choice O
. O

But O
sometimes O
you O
need O
only O
one O
or O
a O
few O
tables B-Data_Structure
to O
be O
schema-flexible O
and O
your O
other O
data O
is O
relational O
. O

Some O
SQL B-Programming_Language
RDBMS B-Application
support O
schema O
flexible O
tables B-Data_Structure
, O
E.g O
. O
SAP O
HANA O
( O
" O

TABLE O
.. O
. O
WITH O
SCHEMA O
FLEXIBILITY O
.. O
. O
" O
) O
. O

, O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
25610261 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/25610261/ O


The O
notation O
{url}foo O
is O
used O
to O
refer O
to O
an O
expanded O
name O
whose O
namespace O
part O
is O
url O
and O
whose O
local O
name O
part O
is O
foo O
. O

It O
's O
sometimes O
referred O
to O
as O
' O
Clark O
notation O
' O
for O
James O
Clark O
, O
who O
promoted O
it O
. O

When O
this O
notation O
is O
in O
use O
, O
unqualified O
names O
are O
sometimes O
referred O
to O
using O
the O
notation O
{}foo O
and O
sometimes O
( O
as O
in O
your O
error O
message O
) O
using O
the O
notation O
foo O
. O

The O
error O
message O
is O
telling O
you O
that O
it O
has O
found O
an O
element O
with O
the O
unqualified O
name O
foo O
, O
at O
a O
location O
where O
it O
was O
expecting O
a O
namespace-qualfied O
element O
named O
either O
foo O
or O
bar O
in O
the O
namespace O
url O
. O

Probable O
cause O
: O
the O
XML B-Programming_Language
instance O
lacks O
a O
required O
namespace O
declaration O
. O

NO O
. O

There O
is O
no O
way O
to O
get O
certificate O
out O
of O
Windows B-Application
Azure I-Application
. O

Question O
is O
how O
it O
( O
the O
certificate O
) O
appeared O
in O
the O
Azure B-Application
at O
first O
place O
. O

It O
was O
certainly O
not O
uploaded O
by O
Microsoft O
people O
or O
some O
magic O
. O

It O
is O
a O
developer O
who O
packed O
the O
deployment O
package O
to O
include O
the O
certificate O
reference O
( O
thumbprint O
) O
and O
service O
administrator O
( O
or O
co-admin O
) O
who O
uploaded O
the O
original O
certificate O
in O
the O
Azure B-Application
. O

So O
contact O
that O
people O
( O
whom O
might O
be O
just O
you O
? O
) O

and O
ask O
for O
the O
original O
certificate O
. O

If O
certificate O
is O
lost O
, O
contact O
the O
original O
issuer O
( O
certification O
authority O
) O
for O
a O
copy O
, O
if O
you O
were O
the O
one O
to O
originally O
requested O
. O

If O
you O
did O
not O
originally O
requested O
the O
certificate O
, O
there O
might O
have O
been O
a O
reason O
behind O
that O
. O

If O
you O
know O
your O
max O
value O
for O
your O
numbers O
and O
can O
afford O
to O
keep O
a O
list B-Data_Structure
of O
primes O
, O
then O
factoring O
them O
may O
be O
a O
better O
solution O
for O
the O
average/random O
case O
. O

Otherwise O
, O
worst O
case O
complexity O
, O
it O
's O
still O
O(N*N) O
- O
think O
" O
all O
of O
them O
are O
primes O
" O
for O
the O
worst O
case O
. O

Approach O
: O

factor O
them O
and O
store O
a O
Map[N] O
+ O
int O
closestNeigh[] O

take O
a O
factor O
and O
O(N) O
determine O
for O
each O
of O
them O
the O
closest O
that O
contain O
that O
factor O
( O
prefix/sufix O
sums O
will O
be O
involved O
) O

eliminate O
that O
factor O
from O
all O
the O
factor O
maps O

take O
the O
next O
factor O
. O

Adjust O
the O
closest O
neighbor O
index O
only O
if O
new O
one O
is O
closest O
. O

This O
may O
bring O
some O
" O
relief O
" O
on O
the O
line O
of O
O O
( O
N* O
<num_distict_factors> O
) O
, O
but O
again O
if O
<num_distict_factors> O
== O
N O
( O
all O
primes O
) O
, O
then O
it O
is O
still O
O(N*N) O

When O
you O
save O
the O
file O
in O
Notepad B-Application
, O
the O
file O
is O
reencoded O
to O
be O
saved O
as O
your O
default O
file O
encoding O
for O
your O
Windows B-Operating_System
installation O
. O

Notepad B-Application
auto-detected O
the O
encoding O
when O
it O
opened O
the O
file O
, O
however O
. O

Python B-Programming_Language
opens O
file O
using O
that O
same O
system O
encoding O
, O
by O
default O
, O
which O
is O
why O
you O
can O
now O
open O
the O
file O
. O

Quoting O
the O
open() O
function O
documentation O
: O

OP_BLOCK O
: O
( O
output O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

You O
'll O
have O
to O
explicitly O
specify O
the O
correct O
encoding O
for O
the O
file O
if O
you O
wanted O
to O
open O
it O
directly O
in O
Python B-Programming_Language
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_3408 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

I O
used O
' O
utf-8-sig O
' O
as O
an O
example O
here O
, O
as O
that O
is O
a O
file O
encoding O
that O
Notepad B-Application
can O
auto-detect O
. O

It O
could O
well O
be O
that O
the O
encoding O
is O
UTF-16 O
or O
plain O
UTF-8 O
or O
any O
number O
of O
other O
encodings O
, O
however O
. O

If O
you O
think O
that O
the O
page O
is O
encoded O
with O
a O
specific O
ANSI O
codepage O
you O
still O
have O
to O
name O
the O
exact O
codepage O
. O

Your O
system O
is O
configured O
to O
use O
code O
page O
936 O
( O
GBK O
) O
but O
that O
is O
not O
the O
correct O
encoding O
for O
this O
file O
. O

See O
the O
codecs B-Library
module O
for O
a O
list O
of O
supported O
encodings O
. O

As O
scrapy B-Library
is O
open O
source O
and O
also O
has O
plenty O
of O
extension O
points O
, O
this O
should O
be O
doable O
. O

The O
requests O
are O
finally O
assembled O
and O
sent O
out O
in O
scrapy/core/downloader/handlers/http11.py O
in O
ScrapyAgent.download_request O
( O
https://github.com/scrapy/scrapy/blob/master/scrapy/core/downloader/handlers/http11.py#L270 O
) O

If O
you O
place O
your O
hook O
there O
you O
can O
dump O
the O
request O
type O
, O
request O
headers O
, O
and O
request O
body O
. O

To O
place O
your O
code O
there O
you O
can O
either O
try O
monkey O
patching O
ScrapyAgent.download_request O
or O
to O
subclass O
ScrapyAgent B-Library_Class
to O
do O
the O
request O
logging O
, O
then O
subclass O
HTTP11DownloadHandler B-Library_Class
to O
use O
your O
Scrapy B-Library
Agent O
and O
then O
set O
HTTP11DownloadHandler B-Library_Class
as O
new O
DOWNLOAD_HANDLER B-Library_Class
for O
http O
/ O
https O
requests O
in O
your O
project O
's O
settings.py O
( O
for O
details O
see O
: O
https://doc.scrapy.org/en/latest/topics/settings.html#download-handlers O
) O

In O
my O
opinion O
this O
is O
the O
closest O
you O
can O
get O
to O
logging O
the O
requests O
going O
out O
without O
using O
a O
packet O
sniffer O
or O
a O
logging O
proxy O
( O
which O
might O
be O
a O
bit O
overkill O
for O
your O
scenario O
) O
. O

: O

( O

for O

CODE_BLOCK O

This O
is O
a O
multi O
threaded O
scenario O
. O

The O
main O
thread O
handles O
the O
application O
and O
UI O
events O
, O
and O
it O
starts O
up O
a O
new O
thread O
to O
do O
some O
background O
operations O
. O

The O
" O
background O
" O
thread O
loads O
the O
data O
from O
files O
into O
a O
data-table O
of O
a O
strongly-typed O
dataset O
. O

The O
DataGridView B-Library_Class
is O
bound O
to O
that O
DataTable B-Library_Class
. O

Once O
the O
data O
is O
ready O
, O
the O
" O
background O
" O
thread O
invokes O
the O
refresh() O
function O
of O
the O
DataGridView B-Library_Class
on O
the O
form O
. O

If O
there O
are O
more O
lines O
then O
what O
fits O
on O
one O
screen B-Device
and O
the O
vertical B-User_Interface_Element
scrollbar I-User_Interface_Element
is O
to O
appear O
: O
the O
grid B-User_Interface_Element
crashes O
. O

The O
new O
datalines B-User_Interface_Element
are O
always O
displayed O
. O

Error O
only O
occurs O
if O
there O
are O
enough O
lines O
to O
display O
the O
scrollbar B-User_Interface_Element
( O
see O
image B-User_Interface_Element
below O
) O
. O

I O
use O
.NET B-Library
3.5 O
. O

In O
Windows B-Operating_System
XP O
it O
crashes O
the O
whole O
application O
. O

On O
Win B-Operating_System
7 O
( O
64 O
bit O
) O
only O
the O
grid B-User_Interface_Element
becomes O
unresponsive O
, O
but O
once O
I O
resize O
the O
window B-User_Interface_Element

scrollbar B-User_Interface_Element
appears O
and O
all O
is O
fine O
. O

relevant O
parts O
of O
the O
code O
are O
attached O
below O
. O

operation O

The O
general O
way O
to O
achieve O
your O
requirement O
is O
to O
implement O
an O
ICommand B-Library_Class
type O
Attached O
Property O
for O
each O
event O
that O
you O
want O
to O
replace O
. O

The O
basic O
idea O
is O
this. O
. O
add O
an O
ICommand B-Library_Class
Attached O
Property O
with O
a O
PropertyChangedCallback B-Library_Class
handler O
. O

In O
this O
handler O
( O
which O
will O
be O
called O
when O
an O
ICommand B-Library_Class
is O
data O
bound O
to O
this O
property O
) O
, O
attach O
a O
handler O
to O
the O
event O
that O
you O
want O
to O
handle O
. O

Then O
, O
when O
that O
event O
is O
called O
, O
just O
execute O
the O
ICommand B-Library_Class
instance O
. O

So O
you O
can O
handle O
the O
event O
in O
your O
view O
model O
via O
the O
ICommand B-Library_Class
instance O
. O

is O
an O
example O
using O
the O

event O
: O

41325590 O

You O
're O
using O
fancy O
quotes O
in O
your O
assignment O
of O
export_folder_path O
. O

These O
slanted O
Unicode O
quotes O
are O
not O
recognized O
as O
quotes O
by O
bash B-Application
, O
and O
are O
therefore O
treated O
as O
literals O
. O

This O
is O
usually O
due O
to O
copypasting O
from O
blogs O
, O
or O
using O
an O
editor B-Application
or O
OS O
not O
intended O
for O
programmers O
such O
as O
Word B-Application
or O
macOS B-Operating_System
. O

Replace O
them O
with O
regular O
ASCII O
double O
quotes O
in O
your O
script O
, O
and O
disable O
" O
smart O
quotes O
" O
in O
your O
editor B-Application
or O
OS O
. O

this O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_5920 O
( O

for O

) O

The O
double O
quotes O
will O
take O
care O
of O
any O
spaces O
in O
the O
name O
of O
the O
directory O
. O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
10116412 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10116412/ O


The O
get* O
and O
set* O
style O
of O
naming O
is O
specified O
in O
the O
JavaBeans B-Library_Class
specification O
, O
and O
some O
libraries O
using O
reflection O
expect O
this O
style O
to O
be O
used O
. O

For O
example O
, O
Jackson B-Library_Class
mapper I-Library_Class
can O
serialize O
a O
java B-Programming_Language
object O
using O
the O
get/setters O
to O
JSON O
without O
any O
additional O
annotations O
; O
if O
you O
use O
a O
different O
naming O
style O
, O
you O
have O
to O
tell O
it O
where O
your O
properties O
are O
. O

Note O
that O
some O
other O
programming O
languages O
use O
different O
styles O
. O

Perl B-Programming_Language
libraries O
, O
for O
example O
, O
often O
use O
a O
->someProperty() O
getter O
and O
->someProperty($newValue) O
setter O
. O

Matplotlib B-Library
" O
snaps O
" O
plot O
limits O
to O
" O
whole O
" O
( O
factors O
of O
2 O
, O
5 O
, O
10 O
, O
100 O
, O
etc O
) O
numbers O
, O
by O
default O
. O

This O
often O
means O
that O
your O
data O
may O
wind O
up O
on O
the O
boundary O
of O
the O
plot O
. O

ax.margins O
allows O
you O
to O
add O
a O
padding O
factor O
before O
this O
autoscaling O
for O
the O
plot O
is O
calculated O
. O

It O
's O
a O
quick O
way O
to O
avoid O
the O
problem O
of O
points O
on O
the O
plot O
boundary O
. O

through O

. O

to O

. O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
22814259 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22814259/ O


Caching O
System.Drawing B-Library_Class
objects O
is O
a O
mistake O
. O

They O
are O
very O
cheap O
to O
create O
, O
very O
expensive O
to O
keep O
around O
. O

They O
are O
allocated O
on O
a O
special O
heap B-Data_Structure
that O
all O
processes O
on O
a O
desktop B-Device
need O
to O
share O
. O

The O
heap B-Data_Structure
size O
is O
limited O
to O
65535 O
objects O
. O

Creating O
objects O
like O
a O
brush B-Library_Class
or O
a O
pen B-Library_Class
takes O
roughly O
a O
microsecond O
, O
miniscule O
compared O
to O
the O
cost O
of O
the O
operation O
you O
perform O
with O
them O
. O

The O
only O
drawing O
object O
that O
is O
expensive O
is O
a O
Font B-Library_Class
. O

Creating O
one O
involves O
a O
sizable O
chunk O
of O
overhead O
taken O
by O
the O
font B-Library_Class
mapper O
. O

But O
that O
's O
already O
solved O
by O
.NET B-Library
, O
it O
caches O
them O
. O

Other O
than O
hogging O
the O
heap B-Data_Structure
needlessly O
, O
the O
programming O
style O
is O
dangerous O
. O

It O
is O
far O
too O
easy O
to O
forget O
blindly O
applying O
the O
using O
statement O
. O

This O
certainly O
can O
get O
you O
into O
trouble O
, O
you O
are O
relying O
on O
the O
finalizer O
thread O
to O
release O
them O
again O
. O

If O
a O
program O
involves O
lots O
of O
heavy O
painting O
but O
not O
enough O
object O
allocation O
to O
trigger O
a O
GC O
then O
you O
will O
exhaust O
the O
quota O
for O
GDI B-Library
objects O
. O

Which O
is O
10,000 O
objects O
for O
a O
process O
by O
default O
. O

This O
will O
crash O
your O
program O
. O

Do O
note O
that O
the O
System.Drawing B-Library_Class
class O
wrappers O
are O
not O
nearly O
big O
enough O
to O
trigger O
a O
GC O
by O
themselves O
, O
10000 O
of O
them O
will O
not O
be O
enough O
to O
get O
the O
finalizers O
to O
run O
and O
release O
the O
handles O
again O
. O

The O
problem O
is O
very O
easy O
to O
diagnose O
, O
you O
can O
use O
Task B-Application
Manager I-Application
. O

Use O
View O
+ O
Select O
Columns B-User_Interface_Element
and O
tick O
" O
GDI O
Objects O
" O
. O

Might O
as O
well O
tick O
" O
USER O
Objects O
" O
, O
another O
one O
that O
's O
very O
easily O
leaked O
. O

Keep O
an O
eye O
on O
the O
displayed O
counts O
for O
your O
process O
while O
you O
are O
using O
it O
. O

A O
steadily O
climbing O
number O
spells O
doom O
. O

There O
is O
no O
out O
of O
the O
box O
ability O
to O
set O
the O
width O
and O
height O
for O

dialogs B-User_Interface_Element
in O

7.5 O
( O
it O
's O
available O
in O
8.0 O
) O

, O

could O
customize O
the O
\sitecore\shell\Controls\jQueryModalDialogs.html O
file O
. O

Just O
find O
and O

Your O
NSURLConnection B-Library_Class
's O
callbacks O
are O
happening O
on O
the O
main O
queue B-Data_Structure
. O

This O
is O
one O
reason O
your O
application O
is O
locking O
up O
. O

Your O
managed O
object O
context O
, O
at O
least O
in O
the O
code O
you O
have O
posted O
, O
is O
not O
following O
the O
Core B-Library
Data I-Library
concurrency O
rules O
. O

You O
have O
a O
choice O
between O
thread O
confinement O
( O
unfortunately O
, O
the O
default O
, O
which O
is O
obsolete O
) O
, O
and O
queue B-Data_Structure
confinement O
. O

With O
thread O
confinement O
, O
you O
can O
only O
use O
a O
managed O
object O
context O
from O
the O
thread O
where O
it O
was O
created O
. O

If O
you O
created O
your O
managed O
object O
context O
on O
the O
main O
thread O
( O
or O
queue B-Data_Structure
) O
, O
you O
can O
only O
use O
it O
from O
there O
- O
so O
any O
Core B-Library
Data I-Library
operation O
you O
perform O
on O
that O
context O
will O
block O
the O
main O
thread O
, O
and O
in O
turn O
the O
UI O
. O

Using O
queue B-Data_Structure
confinement O
( O
almost O
) O
any O
operation O
on O
the O
managed O
object O
context O
must O
go O
through O
either O
the O
performBlock O
: O
or O
performBlockAndWait O
: O
methods O
. O

The O
enqueued O
block O
is O
executed O
on O
the O
context O
's O
serial O
queue B-Data_Structure
. O

This O
is O
far O
less O
failure O
prone O
than O
thread O
confinement O
and O
has O
been O
the O
recommended O
practice O
for O
concurrency O
since O
iOS B-Operating_System
5 O
. O

OP_BLOCK O
: O
( O
output O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

Typically O
this O
would O
be O
done O
using O
an O
NSFetchedResultsController B-Library_Class
, O
which O
observes O
a O
managed O
object O
context O
for O
changes O
relevant O
to O
it O
's O
fetch O
request O
. O

Once O
the O
initial O
fetch O
populates O
the O
controller O
it O
will O
listen O
for O
changes O
to O
the O
context O
that O
affect O
the O
objects O
specified O
by O
the O
fetch O
request O
. O

When O
relevant O
changes O
occur O
the O
controller O
informs O
it O
's O
delegate O
through O
callbacks O
. O

The O
PersistentGenericSet B-Library_Class
is O
part O
of O
NHibernate B-Library
( O
used O
to O
track O
changes O
in O
collections O
) O
. O

It O
is O
based O
on O
the O
ISet B-Library_Class
interface O
and O
classes O
from O
Iesi.Collections B-Library
, O
which O
was O
used O
to O
fill O
a O
gap O
in O
the O
.Net B-Library
framework O
as O
there O
is O
n't O
a O
Set B-Library_Class
type O
. O

I O
guess O
that O
WCF B-Library
has O
a O
problem O
serializing O
this O
type O
. O

A O
quick O
fix O
is O
to O
change O
your O
NHibernate B-Library
mappings O
to O
use O
a O
Bag B-Library_Class
instead O
of O
a O
Set B-Library_Class
. O

Then O
you O
can O
use O
a O
normal O
IList B-Library_Class
<T> I-Library_Class
instead O
of O
Set<T> B-Library_Class
in O
your O
classes O
w O
. O

A O
better O
solution O
is O
to O
create O
a O
remote O
facade O
which O
sends O
DTOs O
to O
your O
WCF B-Library
endpoints O
. O

This O
will O
allow O
you O
to O
keep O
the O
interface O
of O
your O
internal O
types O
separate O
from O
those O
exposed O
as O
remote O
services O
. O

Jimmy O
Bogards O
Automapper B-Library
is O
a O
great O
tool O
which O
will O
help O
with O
the O
mapping O
process O
. O

Edit O

After O
re-reading O
the O
problem O
I O
had O
a O
look O
around O
the O
and O
came O
across O
this O
article O
which O
describes O
a O
workaround O
for O
sending O
NHibernate B-Library
collections O
over O
WCF B-Library
. O

David O
Brion O
has O
written O
a O
good O
follow O
up O
article O
. O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
16434254 O

Question_URL O

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/16434254/ O


When O
assigning O
the O
Registry O
data O
to O
your O
m_reqPath O
variable O
, O
you O
are O
treating O
it O
as O
null-terminated O
character B-Data_Type
data O
. O

However O
, O
string B-Data_Type
data O
read O
by O
RegQueryValueEx() O
is O
not O
guaranteed O
to O
be O
null-terminated O
, O
if O
the O
original O
writer O
of O
the O
data O
did O
not O
include O
one O
. O

This O
is O
clearly O
stated O
in O
the O
documentation O
. O

Chances O
are O
that O
the O
string B-Data_Type
data O
you O
are O
reading O
from O
the O
Registry O
is O
not O
null-terminated O
, O
so O
you O
end O
up O
copying O
random O
data O
from O
the O
end O
of O
your O
buffer B-Library_Class
. O

To O
account O
for O
that O
possibility O
, O
you O
need O
to O
allocate O
extra O
space O
in O
your O
buffer B-Library_Class
and O
put O
your O
own O
null O
terminator O
at O
the O
end O
of O
whatever O
data O
you O
actually O
read O
. O

If O
the O
data O
is O
properly O
null O
terminated O
, O
then O
your O
terminator O
will O
simply O
be O
redundant O
. O

You O
are O
also O
leaking O
the O
opened O
Registry O
key O
handle O
if O
RegOpenKeyEx() O
succeeds O
but O
RegQueryValueEx() O
fails O
. O

Try O
this O
instead O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_2123 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

To O
avoid O
this O
issue O
altogether O
, O
use O
RegGetValue() O
instead O
, O
which O
deals O
with O
the O
null O
terminator O
for O
you O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_2124 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

Or O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_2125 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

An O
AsyncTask B-Library_Class
that O
returns O
nothing O
from O
doInBackground() O
( O
and O
does O
n't O
communicate O
with O
onPostExecute() O
via O
private O
members O
) O
is O
always O
suspicious O
. O

You O
have O
a O
lot O
of O
side O
effects O
in O
your O
AsyncTask B-Library_Class
and O
that O
kind O
of O
stuff O
is O
hard O
to O
debug O
. O

You O
add O
to O
cityList O
and O
activeOrders O
for O
example O
, O
without O
showing O
what O
that O
actually O
is O
. O

Presumably O
those O
are O
lists B-Data_Structure
attached O
to O
some O
Adapter B-Library_Class
and O
adding O
to O
those O
might O
trigger O
a O
View B-Library_Class
attached O
to O
the O
Adapter B-Library_Class
to O
be O
re-drawn O
. O

If O
that O
is O
the O
case O
you O
could O
try O
calling O
setNotifyOnChange(false) O
on O
mAdapter O
( O
to O
delay O
updates O
until O
you O
manually O
call O
notifyDataSetChanged() O
later O
) O
. O

http://developer.android.com/reference/android/widget/ArrayAdapter.html#setNotifyOnChange(boolean) O

In O
general O
, O
if O
your O
AsyncTask B-Library_Class
does O
n't O
return O
anything O
or O
otherwise O
" O
communicate O
" O
with O
onPostExecute() O
there O
is O
little O
point O
in O
having O
onPostExecute() O
in O
the O
first O
place O
. O

Even O
better O
would O
be O
not O
to O
have O
any O
side O
effect O
in O
doInBackground() O
and O
instead O
return O
the O
parsed O
data O
and O
only O
add O
it O
to O
cityList O
and O
activeOrders O
in O
onPostExecute() O
. O

Multi-threading O
is O
tricky O
and O
AsyncTasks B-Library_Class
while O
appearing/attempting O
to O
make O
it O
easier O
, O
have O
many O
pitfalls O
. O

I O
have O
attempted O
to O
answer O
a O
question O
on O
thread O
safety O
of O

here O

( O

) O

item O
. O

The O

to O

and O

. O

What O
you O
are O

. O

the O

can O
not O

a O
blob B-Library
store I-Library
entity O

only O
delete O
it O
. O

have O
no O

over O
the O
blob B-Library_Class
store I-Library_Class
key I-Library_Class
, O
so O

will O

to O

the O
URL O
in O

with O
a O

to O
the O
current O
blob B-Library

. O

the O
array B-Data_Structure
when O

is O
1 O
dimension O
before O

the O

array B-Data_Structure

are O

it O
there O
. O

by O
parent O
then O
sort O
. O

you O
build O
your O
multidimensional O
array B-Data_Structure
, O

will O
be O

to O
the O

. O

already O
in O

, O

up O

I O

it O
out O
. O

sending O
the O

an O

manner O
. O

to O

back O
as O
a O

object O

rather O
than O

and O

it O

as O
a O

. O

is O
how O
I O

to O

Answer_to_Question_ID O

26353240 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26353240/ O


No O
need O
to O
record O
these O
times O
yourself O
. O

The O
Pi B-Device
( O
and O
almost O
any O
Linux B-Operating_System
distribution O
) O
writes O
those O
events O
to O
the O
/var/log/wtmp O
file O
( O
more O
about O
that O
file O
here O
) O
. O

The O
last O
command O
can O
retrieve O
those O
events O
( O
also O
see O
the O
manual O
entry O
for O
last O
) O
. O

Try O
the O
following O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_3634 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

Explanation O
of O
the O
flags O
: O

-F O
prints O
the O
full O
date O
and O
times O
- O
which O
is O
handy O
in O
your O
case O
, O
because O
that O
's O
what O
you O
wanted O
to O
know O
. O

-R O
suppresses O
the O
hostname O
in O
the O
output O
. O

You O
do O
n't O
need O
that O
. O

-x O
shows O
shutdown O
en O
runlevel O
changes O
- O
now O
that O
's O
what O
you O
wanted O
to O
know O
. O

Finally O
the O
grep O
statement O
filters O
out O
the O
boot O
or O
shutdown O
messages O
. O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
26353240 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26353240/ O


I O
would O
recomend O
code O
that O
looks O
like O
the O
following O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_3633 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

The O
couple O
of O
differences O
. O

First O
, O
you O
always O
open O
the O
file B-Library_Class
in O
append O
mode O
. O

This O
way O
, O
the O
file B-Library_Class
will O
be O
flushed O
every O
time O
. O

Next O
, O
it O
will O
always O
update O
the O
file B-Library_Class
with O
the O
amount O
of O
time O
elapsed O
. O

So O
even O
if O
your O
raspberry B-Device
pi I-Device
shuts O
down O
, O
you O
should O
be O
able O
to O
recover O
it O
. O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
37757484 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/37757484/ O


To O
decide O
between O
using O
an O
ArrayList/Vector B-Library_Class
or O
a O
HashMap B-Library_Class
depends O
on O
whether O
you O
have O
key-value O
pairs O
or O
simple O
a O
list B-Data_Structure
of O
elements O
. O

For O
key-value O
pairs O
a O
HashMap B-Library_Class
is O
the O
go-to O
option O
( O
e.g O
name O
- O
person O
object O
) O
. O

If O
you O
just O
have O
objects B-Library_Class
but O
no O
real O
keys O
( O
a O
list O
of O
trees O
in O
a O
forest O
) O
then O
a O
ArrayList B-Library_Class
or O
Vector B-Library_Class
would O
be O
better O
. O

The O
difference O
between O
Vector B-Library_Class
and O
ArrayList B-Library_Class
is O
more O
subtle O
. O

If O
you O
want O
more O
information O
on O
the O
difference O
between O
the O
two O
you O
can O
read O
this O
article O
. O

But O
as O
the O
article O
is O
from O
2001 O
, O
the O
information O
is O
n't O
the O
newest O
. O

In O
most O
cases O
, O
the O
ArrayList B-Library_Class
is O
the O
better O
choice O
and O
Vector B-Library_Class
is O
pretty O
much O
considered O
deprecated O
nowadays O
. O

As O
the O
biggest O
difference O
between O
the O
two O
is O
, O
that O
Vector B-Library_Class
is O
synchronized O
while O
ArrayList B-Library_Class
is O
n't O
, O
which O
in O
most O
cases O
, O
makes O
the O
Vector B-Library_Class
slower O
than O
the O
ArrayList B-Library_Class
as O
it O
creates O
unnecessary O
overhead O
. O

For O
more O
information O
you O
can O
look O
at O
this O
question O
: O
Why O
is O
Java B-Programming_Language

class O

? O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
22773304 O

: O

Many O
decimal O
numbers O
are O
not O
exactly O
representable O
in O
IEEE O
floating O
point O
( O
i.e O
. O
the O
binary O
representation O
used O
for O
double B-Data_Type
) O
and O
0.1 O
falls O
in O
this O
camp O
. O

When O
you O
type O
0.1 O
the O
C++ B-Programming_Language
compiler B-Application
is O
required O
to O
convert O
that O
into O
a O
double B-Data_Type
to O
be O
represented O
on O
your O
hardware O
. O

It O
does O
so O
by O
computing O
a O
near O
approximation O
of O
this O
and O
so O
you O
see O
a O
bit O
of O
error O
. O

If O
you O
try O
something O
like O
a O
power O
of O
two O
: O
0.5 O
, O
0.25 O
these O
will O
be O
exactly O
represented O
. O

See O
this O
link O
for O
a O
much O
more O
in-depth O
description O
of O
the O
idea O
. O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
22773304 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22773304/ O


This O
is O
normal O
behaviour O
in O
any O
computer B-Device
. O

It O
's O
caused O
by O
the O
fact O
that O
decimal B-Data_Type
numbers I-Data_Type
are O
being O
stored O
in O
fixed-sized O
binary O
memory O
. O

The O
extra O
digits O
come O
from O
the O
inherent O
errors O
caused O
by O
converting O
from O
binary O
to O
decimal O
. O

You O
will O
not O
get O
rid O
of O
them O
. O

The O
best O
you O
can O
do O
is O
choose O
a O
precision O
( O
either O
float B-Data_Type
or O
double B-Data_Type
) O
that O
is O
big O
enough O
so O
that O
the O
extra O
error O
digits O
will O
not O
make O
any O
difference O
to O
your O
solution O
, O
and O
then O
chop O
them O
off O
when O
you O
display O
the O
number O
. O

When O
there O
is O
no O
physical O
desktop B-Device
( O
or O
remote B-Application
desktop I-Application
session O
) O
, O
the O
Java B-Programming_Language
process O
that O
runs O
Selenium B-Application
RC I-Application
will O
result O
in O
a O
black O
screenshot O
. O

Without O
knowing O
more O
info O
, O
this O
could O
be O
your O
problem O
. O

As O
the O
creator O
of O
Selenium B-Application
RC I-Application
, O
I O
actually O
recommend O
against O
using O
the O
Windows B-Operating_System
Service O
entirely O
. O

Instead O
, O
do O
what O
we O
do O
at O
BrowserMob B-Application
, O
which O
provides O
free O
monitoring O
and O
free O
load O
testing O
services O
, O
as O
well O
as O
a O
recently O
launch O
instant O
test O
tool O
that O
takes O
screenshots O
of O
your O
site O
from O
multiple O
locations O
. O

What O
we O
do O
is O
launch O
everything O
from O
under O
the O
context O
of O
a O
VNC B-Application
session O
. O

On O
Windows B-Operating_System
, O
configure O
VNC B-Application
to O
launch O
a O
session O
upon O
startup O
. O

Then O
make O
sure O
the O
user O
auto-logs O
in O
. O

Then O
place O
a O
.bat O
file O
in O
Program O
Files->Startup O
that O
launches O
Selenium B-Application
RC I-Application
. O

It O
's O
kind O
of O
a O
pain O
, O
but O
it O
's O
the O
most O
reliable O
way O
I O
've O
found O
for O
ensuring O
that O
Selenium B-Application
RC I-Application
starts O
in O
an O
environment O
that O
supports O
screenshots O
, O
launching O
IE B-Application
, O
interacting O
with O
native O
events O
, O
etc O
. O

Good O
luck O
! O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
5082507 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5082507/ O


" O
how O
to O
fire O
a O
mouse B-Device
down O
event O
? O
" O
. O

You O
do O
not O
need O
to O
worry O
about O
' O
firing O
' O
the O
event O
- O
the O
OS O
does O
that O
. O

You O
need O
to O
handle O
the O
event O
which O
is O
EVT_LEFT_DOWN B-Library_Class
. O

Is O
your O
question O
about O
how O
to O
handle O
wxWidgets B-Library_Class
events I-Library_Class
? O

Have O
you O
looked O
at O
the O
sample O
programs O
? O

http://docs.wxwidgets.org/2.6/wx_samples.html O
They O
are O
all O
in O
C++ B-Programming_Language
. O

There O
is O
a O
description O
of O
how O
to O
handle O
events B-Library_Class
here O
: O
http://docs.wxwidgets.org/2.6/wx_eventhandlingoverview.html#eventhandlingoverview O

If O
you O
question O
is O
about O
something O

AboveNumber B-Library_Class
can O
do O
no O
magic O
. O

If O
the O
list B-Data_Structure
is O
unordered O
, O
it O
must O
run O
through O
all O
items O
in O
the O
list B-Data_Structure
. O

You O
can O
optimize O
this O
by O
maintaining O
the O
list B-Data_Structure
in O
order O
, O
i.e O
. O
by O
making O
sure O
that O
the O
list B-Data_Structure
is O
always O
ordered O
after O
an O
insert O
or O
erase O
. O

If O
the O
list B-Data_Structure
is O
ordered O
, O
you O
may O
find O
your O
" O
mean O
" O
by O
a O
binary O
search O
, O
which O
would O
be O
much O
faster O
than O
running O
through O
all O
the O
list B-Data_Structure
, O
then O
cut O
the O
list B-Data_Structure
at O
that O
position O
. O

OP_BLOCK O
: O
( O
output O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

Waffle B-Library
uses O
the O
Windows B-Application
SSPI I-Application
, O
which O
performs O
all O
operations O
involving O
Kerberos O
tickets O
on O
client B-Application
's O
behalf O
. O

The O
client B-Application
never O
sees O
the O
ticket O
. O

OP_BLOCK O
: O
( O
output O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

This O
is O
a O
basic O
Kerberos O
question O
. O

The O
token O
sent O
to O
the O
server B-Application
is O
encrypted O
by O
server O
's O
secret O
key O
, O
which O
guarantees O
that O
the O
token O
was O
created O
by O
the O
Ticket B-Application
Granting I-Application
Service I-Application
, O
which O
authenticated O
the O
client B-Application
. O

OP_BLOCK O
: O
( O
output O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

Yes O
, O
the O
are O
retrieved O
from O
the O
security O
token O
. O

This O
is O
a O
Windows-specific B-Operating_System
extension O
of O
the O
MIT O
Kerberos O
protocol O
. O

The O
problem O
is O
you O
expect O
that O
Javascript B-Programming_Language
contained O
within O
an O
ajax O
response O
is O
executed O
. O

This O
is O
n't O
the O
case O
, O
the O
browser B-Application
does O
n't O
execute O
any O
Javascript B-Programming_Language
contained O
within O
ajax O
responses O
. O

It O
might O
be O
possible O
to O
try O
to O
parse O
out O
the O
Javascript B-Programming_Language
and O
execute O
it O
in O
some O
way O
, O
such O
as O
eval() O
but O
that O
would O
be O
nasty O
and O
not O
a O
good O
idea O
. O

Using O
eval() O
you O
also O
have O

The O
notion O
that O
it O
is O
bad O
practice O
for O
your O
UI O
to O
create/load/consume O
a O
datatable B-Data_Structure
comes O
from O
the O
idea O
that O
it O
is O
preferable O
to O
split O
your O
application O
into O
layers O
that O
specialize O
, O
the O
most O
common O
split O
is O
to O
have O
3 O
layers O
: O

Layer O
1 O
is O
a O
data O
layer O
responsible O
for O
communicating O
with O
the O
database O
and O
populating O
domain O
objects O
, O
the O
domain O
objects O
are O
typically O
defined O
in O
layer O
2 O
which O
also O
holds O
the O
business O
logic O
for O
your O
application O
. O

by O
domain O
objects O
i O
mean O
classes O
that O
represent O
real O
things O
like O
customer O
, O
bank O
account O
, O
hotel O
room O
etc O
. O

and O
by O
business O
logic O
i O
mean O
the O
rules O
that O
apply O
to O
domain O
objects O
during O
events O
i.e O
. O
when O
a O
hotel O
room O
is O
booked O
a O
confirmation O
is O
sent O
to O
the O
customer O
. O

the O
third O
layer O
is O
the O
UI O
layer O
, O
to O
simplyfy O
coding O
this O
should O
only O
deal O
with O
whats O
in O
layer O
2 O
, O
this O
is O
where O
the O
recommendation O
to O
not O
use O
datatables B-Data_Structure
in O
your O
UI O
comes O
from O
. O

the O
motivation O
to O
split O
your O
application O
really O
start O
to O
make O
sense O
when O
your O
application O
is O
big O
, O
or O
you O
have O
multiple O
developers O
working O
on O
it O
, O
or O
your O
using O
unit O
testing O
. O

If O
you O
're O
in O
that O
situation O
then O
i O
'd O
try O
and O
find O
a O
friendly O
member O
of O
your O
team O
to O
explain O
this O
better O
, O
but O
if O
this O
is O
just O
you O
writing O
an O
application O
on O
your O
own O
then O
i O
would O
n't O
worry O
too O
much O
about O
it O
, O
write O
lots O
of O
code O
, O
read O
lots O
of O
books O
and O
this O
stuff O
will O
make O
more O
sense O
, O
i O
would O
recommend O
the O
craig O
larman O

uml B-Programming_Language

OP_BLOCK O
: O
( O
output O

for O
annotation O

That O
's O
correct O
, O
and O
I O
explained O
this O
in O

here O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/a/23627479/388980 O

.. O
. O
which O
I O
'm O
assuming O
you O
have O
already O
seen O
, O
since O
you O
commented O
on O
my O
answer O
yesterday O
. O

The O
reason O
that O
@IfProfileValue B-Library_Class
has O
nothing O
to O
do O
with O
@Profile B-Library_Class
or O
@ActiveProfiles B-Library_Class
is O
due O
to O
the O
evolution O
of O
the O
framework O
. O

See O
below O
for O
further O
details O
. O

OP_BLOCK O
: O
( O
output O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

These O
statements O
are O
not O
entirely O
correct O
, O
especially O
the O
last O
part O
. O

@Profile B-Library_Class
is O
used O
to O
selectively O
enable O
a O
component O
( O
e.g O
. O
, O
@Service B-Library_Class
, O
etc O
. O
) O
, O
@Configuration B-Library_Class
class O
, O
or O
@Bean O
method O
if O
one O
of O
the O
named O
bean O
definition O
profiles O
is O
active O
in O
the O
Spring B-Library_Class
Environment I-Library_Class
for O
the O
ApplicationContext B-Library_Class
. O

This O
annotation O
is O
not O
directly O
related O
to O
testing O
: O
@Profile B-Library_Class
should O
not O
be O
used O
on O
a O
test O
class O
. O

@ActiveProfiles B-Library_Class
is O
used O
to O
designate O
which O
bean O
definition O
profiles O
( O
e.g O
. O
, O
those O
declared O
via O
@Profile B-Library_Class
) O
should O
be O
active O
when O
loading O
an O
ApplicationContext B-Library_Class
for O
an O
integration O
test O
. O

@IfProfileValue B-Library_Class
does O
not O
allow O
you O
to O
check O
things O
in O
the O
Spring B-Library_Class
Environment I-Library_Class
. O

I O
'm O
not O
sure O
why O
you O
are O
assuming O
this O
, O
since O
none O
of O
the O
documentation O
in O
the O
Spring B-Library
Framework I-Library
states O
that O
. O

As O
I O
stated O
in O
the O
aforementioned O
thread O
: O

Please O
note O
that O
@IfProfileValue B-Library_Class
was O
introduced O
in O
Spring B-Library
Framework I-Library
2.0 O
, O
long O
before O
the O
notion O
of O
bean O
definition O
profiles O
, O
and O
@ActiveProfiles B-Library_Class
was O
first O
introduced O
in O
Spring B-Library
Framework I-Library
3.1 O
. O

In O
the O
aforementioned O
thread O
, O
I O
also O
pointed O
out O
the O
following O
: O

The O
term O
' O
profile O
' O
is O
perhaps O
misleading O
when O
considering O
the O
semantics O
for O
@IfProfileValue B-Library_Class
. O

The O
key O
is O
to O
think O
about O
' O
test O
groups O
' O
( O
like O
those O
in O
TestNG B-Library
) O
instead O
of O
' O
profiles O
' O
. O

See O
the O
examples O
in O
the O
JavaDoc O
for O
@IfProfileValue B-Library_Class
. O

OP_BLOCK O
: O
( O
output O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

That O
depends O
, O
and O
.. O
. O

I O
'm O
assuming O
you O
mean O
bean O
definition O
profile O
when O
you O
say O
" O
profile O
" O
. O

If O
you O
're O
using O
@ActiveProfiles B-Library_Class
to O
set O
the O
bean O
definition O
profiles O
for O
your O
tests O
, O
you O
cannot O
currently O
use O
@IfProfileValue B-Library_Class
to O
determine O
if O
a O
bean O
definition O
profile B-Library_Class
is O
active O
, O
since O
the O
bean O
definition O
profiles O
configured O
via O
@ActiveProfiles B-Library_Class
are O
set O
directly O
in O
the O
test O
's O
ApplicationContext B-Library_Class
and O
not O
as O
a O
Java B-Programming_Language
system O
property O
. O

However O
, O
if O
you O
are O
setting O
the O
bean O
definition O
profiles O
only O
via O
the O
spring.profiles.active O
system O
property O
, O
then O

would O
be O
possible O
to O
use O
@IfProfileValue B-Library_Class
to O
determine O
if O
a O
bean O
definition O
profile O
is O
active O
, O
since O
@IfProfileValue B-Library_Class
in O
fact O
works O
with O
system O
properties O
. O

For O
example O
, O
you O
could O
then O
use O
the O
following O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_4699 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

OP_BLOCK O
: O
( O
output O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

That O
wo O
n't O
work O
since O
activeProfiles O
is O
the O
incorrect O
property O
name O
. O

The O
correct O
system O
property O
name O
is O
spring.profiles.active O
. O

See O
AbstractEnvironment.ACTIVE_PROFILES_PROPERTY_NAME O
for O
details O
. O

The O
fact O

@IfProfileValue B-Library_Class
does O
not O
work O

harmony O

@ActiveProfiles B-Library_Class
is O
a O

Please O

https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-7754 O

https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-11677 O

Hope O
this O
clarifies O

Sam O

I O
sussed O
it O
. O

The O

I O
was O
having O
was O
that O
the O

was O
not O
being O
called O
in O
the O
AsyncTask B-Library_Class
. O

The O

for O
this O
was O
that O
although O
I O
'd O
created O
and O
prepared O
a O
lopper O
in O
the O
thread O
I O
had O
n't O
called O
Looper.Loop() O

I O
start O
the O
requestLocationUpdates B-Library_Class
, O
kick O
off O
a O
timer O
. O

Either O
the O
locationmanager B-Library_Class
responds O
with O
a O
location O
, O
or O
the O
timer O
expires O
. O

this O
point O
I O
call O

to O
ensure O
things O
return O
to O
normal O
. O

Seems O
to O
be O
working O
. O

You O
also O
have O
to O
remember O
to O
respond O
to O
the O
back O
button B-User_Interface_Element
etc O
, O

. O

No O
, O
it O
's O
not O
a O
bug O
. O

It O
's O
unusual O
, O
but O
it O
's O
not O
a O
bug O
. O

The O
first O
thing O
to O
do O
is O
simplify O
the O
example O
massively O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_4546 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

Result O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_4547 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

Now O
admittedly O
I O
'm O
using O
strings B-Data_Type
for O
both O
start O
and O
end O
, O
but O
due O
to O
+ O
being O
left-associative O
, O
that O
does O
n't O
make O
any O
difference O
here O
. O

( O
If O
start O
were O
an O
integer B-Data_Type
, O
the O
first O
binary O
+ O
operator O
would O
be O
integer B-Data_Type
addition O
in O
both O
cases O
. O
) O

Basically O
, O
the O
extra O
+ O
ends O
up O
being O
a O
unary B-Data_Type
+ O
operator O
with O
' O
\t O
' O
as O
the O
operand O
. O

Unary O
numeric O
promotion O
is O
applied O
to O
the O
char B-Data_Type
, O
giving O
int B-Data_Type
as O
a O
result O
. O

So O
the O
code O
becomes O
effectively O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_4548 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

which O
is O
effectively O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_4549 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

which O
is O
effectively O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_4550 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

.. O
. O
at O
which O
point O
it O
's O
hopefully O
clear O
why O
you O
're O
getting O
the O
output O
you O
are O
. O

To O
avoid O
accidentally O
ending O
up O
treating O
a O
character B-Data_Type
as O
an O
integer B-Data_Type
, O
it O
's O

to O
just O
use O
strings B-Data_Type

at O

code O
wo O

compile O

The O
problem O
is O
not O
just O
with O
the O
+ O
+ O
in O
your O
code O
. O

But O
it O
's O
also O
with O
the O
fact O
that O
you O
are O
using O
char B-Data_Type
' O
\t O
' O
and O
not O
String B-Data_Type
" O
\t O
" O
. O

So O
when O
you O
use O
System.out.println O
( O
" O
Hello O
" O
+ O
' O
\t' O
) O
; O
, O
the O
\t O
is O
taken O
as O
a O
character O
literal O
and O
appended O
to O
the O
string B-Data_Type
as O
\t O
. O

But O
when O
you O
use O
System.out.println O
( O
" O
Hello O
" O
+ O
+ O
' O
\t' O
) O
; O
, O
it O
becomes O
effectively O
System.out.println O
( O
" O
Hello O
" O
+ O
( O
+ O
' O
\t' O
) O
) O
; O
. O

So O
it O
is O
treated O
as O
an O
int B-Data_Type
by O
java B-Programming_Language
. O

You O
only O
assign O
+ O
and O
- O
signs O
to O
ints B-Data_Type
, O
not O
chars B-Data_Type
. O

Remember O
you O
can O
do O
int O
i O
= O
+2 O
or O
-2 O
or O
+ O
+ O
2 O
. O

And O
the O
ASCII O
value O
of O
\t O
is O
9 O
. O

Hence O
it O
gets O
appended O
to O
the O
string B-Data_Type
and O
get O
's O
printed O
as O
Hello9 O
. O

greatly O

. O

are O

jobs O

can O

of O
stored O

to O

tasks I-Application
. O

Since O

've O
tagged O
this O
question O
with O
mysql B-Application
, O
I O
'll O
assume O
thats O
what O
your O
running O
. O

One O
way O
to O
do O
this O
on O
mysql B-Application
is O
: O

http://dev.mysql.com/tech-resources/articles/event-feature.html O

all O
else O
fails O
, O

these O

This O
kind O
of O
syntax O
is O
really O
the O
target O
for O
pyparsing B-Library
. O

The O
basic O
format O
is O
simple O
enough O
, O
and O
in O
pyparsing B-Library
, O
it O
looks O
like O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_558 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

But O
once O
you O
start O
to O
add O
arithmetic O
expressions O
, O
and O
boolean O
operations O
and O
support O
for O
' O
and O
' O
and O
' O
or O
' O
operators O
, O
things O
get O
complicated O
. O

Also O
, O
this O
is O
a O
recursive O
grammar O
, O
since O
an O

can O
itself O
be O
a O
nested O
decision O
. O

Pyparsing B-Library
has O
built-in O
support O
that O
simplifies O
definition O
of O
arithmetic O
and O
boolean B-Data_Type
expressions O
, O
including O
precedence O
of O
operations O
and O

plus O
recursive O

. O

Here O
is O

various O

. O

First O

are O

of O

: O

: O

( O
code O

for O
annotation O
) O

will O
automatically O
convert O

to O

. O

The O

class O
takes O
two O
strings B-Data_Type
: O
a O
string B-Data_Type
containing O
all O
valid O
leading O
characters O
, O
and O
a O
string B-Data_Type
of O
all O

characters O
. O

This O

definition O
supports O
variable O
names O
similar O
to O

. O

Pyparsing B-Library
has O

, O

, O

, O

. O

( O

Now O

Cronjobs B-Application
cannot O
be O
set O
like O
that O
. O

Each O
minute O
the O
cron B-Application
deamon I-Application
looks O
for O
which O
jobs O
to O
run O
based O
on O
the O
pattern O
( O
" O
is O
this O
the O
correct O
weekday O
? O

is O
this O
the O
correct O
minute O
? O
" O

and O
so O
on O
) O
. O

You O
will O
need O
to O
set O
up O
a O
script O
check O
to O
see O
if O
the O
date O
is O
correct O
because O
cron B-Application
cannot O
do O
that O
. O

You O
can O
make O
that O
check O
in O
the O
manual O
job O
or O
in O
Bash B-Application
. O

Well O
, O
1) O
size_t B-Data_Type
is O
a O
typedef O
and O
varies O
with O
architectures O
and O
2) O
Would O
n't O
it O
make O
sense O
to O
have O
the O
largest O
integer B-Data_Type
as O
a O
return O
value O
? O

bits O
? O

Why O
not O

? O

It O
's O

on O
your O
machine O
because O
that O
's O
the O
max O
string B-Data_Type
length O
possible O
. O

through O
the O
package B-Application
manager I-Application
, O

're O
going O
to O
get O
an O

. O

There O

manager I-Application

namely O
, O

your O
entire O
system O
up-to-date O
( O
by O
Ubuntu B-Operating_System
's O

of O
up-to-date O
) O
. O

There O
are O
also O
obvious O
benefits O
to O
following O
a O
given O
piece O
of O
software O
's O
instructions O
. O

Personally O

I O

. O

AS O
@TheESJ O
said O
the O
awaits O
make O
your O
code O
execute O
in O
a O
serial O
fashion O
. O

That O
is O
once O
execution O
reaches O
the O
first O
await O
, O
execution O
is O
effectively O
" O
paused O
" O
and O
will O
not O
resume O
until O
that O
Task B-Library_Class
is O
complete O
. O

You O
can O
avoid O
this O
by O
not O
awaiting O
the O
Task B-Library_Class
, O
just O
add O
it O
to O
a O
list B-Data_Structure
of O
tasks B-Library_Class
to O
keep O
track O
of O
. O

To O
facilitate O
this O
I O
think O
it O
will O
help O
if O
you O
introduced O
a O
couple O
of O
helper O
methods O
to O
execute O
the O
body O
of O
your O
loops O
and O
return O
a O
Task B-Library_Class
. O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_3234 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

Then O
in O
your O
main O
loop O
you O
just O
add O
the O
tasks B-Library_Class
to O
a O
list B-Data_Structure
as O
the O
methods O
are O
kicked O
off O
, O
this O
will O
essentially O
execute O
the O
tasks B-Library_Class
in O
parallel O
. O

You O
may O
need O
to O
increase O
the O
number O
of O
concurrent O
connections O
your O
server B-Application
can O
make O
if O
it O
causes O
a O
problem O
. O

Your O
main O
method O
then O
becomes O
. O

@media O
MIN-width O
: O

Min-width O
media O
queries O
are O
very O
easy O
, O
to O
use O
, O
and O
are O
not O
too O
different O
from O
using O
MAX O
media O
queries O
. O

Here O
is O
an O
example O
using O
your O
code O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_3780 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

It O
is O
important O
to O
still O
use O
max-width O
to O
create O
limits O
for O
the O
style O
of O
objects O
on O
certain O
screens B-Device
. O

Using O
min-width O
can O
be O
especially O
useful O
if O
you O
want O
certain O
styles O
to O
apply O
to O
a O
smaller O
object O
and O
then O
have O
that O
same O
style O
apply O
to O
a O
larger O
object O
. O

This O
way O
you O
can O
keep O
the O
styles O
for O
that O
minimum O
size O
but O
also O
add O
on O
extra O
styles O
to O
the O
larger O
object O
with O
out O
effecting O
the O
smaller O
one O
. O

For O
example O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_3781 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

In O
the O
above O
example O
, O
the O
styles O
from O
screens B-Device
with O
a O
size O
of O
over O
740px O
will O
already O
be O
applied O
to O
any O
screens B-Device
with O
a O
size O
of O
over O
900px O
. O

From O
there O
you O
can O
adjust O
your O
styles O
as O
you O
like O
, O
reducing O
the O
amount O
of O
code O
needed O
to O
produce O
the O
page O
. O

Other O
Things O
: O

-When O
it O
comes O
to O
actual O
elements O
on O
the O
screen B-Device
( O
excluding O
min/max O
-sizes O
with O
@media O
) O
it O
can O
always O
be O
helpful O
to O
use O
percentages O
, O
because O
that O
way O
items O
can O
be O
auto O
re-sized O
according O
to O
the O
screen O
size O
. O

-Here O
is O
a O
great O
website O
that O
will O
help O
you O
on O
your O
endeavours O
with O
media O
queries O
: O
http://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/media-queries-for-standard-devices/ O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
27283346 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27283346/ O


It O
totally O
depends O
on O
the O
rest O
of O
your O
site O
. O

Some O
sites O
can O
be O
displayed O
well O
at O
the O
width O
of O
400px O
while O
some O
others O
need O
to O
set O
a O
minumum O
because O
it O
's O
too O
small O
to O
render O
the O
document O
objects O
in O
a O
clean O
manner O
. O

Very O
often O
you O
will O
not O
even O
need O
to O
use O
min-width O
or O
max-width O
when O
optimizing O
for O
mobile O
, O
there O
are O
far O
more O
better O
practices O
. O

Here O
are O
some O
of O
them O
: O

Use O
Em O
over O
Px O
- O
It O
is O
always O
better O
to O
set O
font-size O
and O
other O
sizes O
in O
units O
of O
" O
em O
" O
rather O
than O
in O
" O
px O
" O
. O

This O
is O
because O
a O
pixel O
is O
extremely O
small O
on O
a O
cell B-Device
phone I-Device
, O
whereas O
em O
units O
proportionally O
adjusts O
the O
object O
to O
a O
size O
that O
fits O
the O
screen B-Device
. O

Use O
Percentages O
- O
You O
'll O
find O
that O
using O
percentages O
are O
far O
more O
friendly O
than O
, O
for O
instance O
, O
specifying O
the O
width O
or O
height O
of O
an O
element O
in O
pixels O
or O
em O
. O

If O
you O
use O
percentages O
, O
your O
content O
will O
always O
adjust O
well O
in O
for O
skinny O
displays O
. O

Avoid O
Absolutely O
Positioned O
Elements O
- O
Having O
elements O
positioned O
absolutely O
can O
be O
more O
difficuly O
to O
handle O
on O
small O
displays O
. O

It O
simply O
can O
, O
as O
the O
absolute O
elements O
may O
get O
too O
near O
to O
the O
relatively O
positioned O
elements O
. O

Use O
relative O
positioning O
as O
much O
as O
possible O
for O
a O
clean O
site O
. O

, O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
21818346 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/21818346/ O


Dump O
the O
pk/clustered O
key O
of O
all O
the O
records O
you O
want O
to O
update O
into O
a O
temp O
table B-Library_Class
. O

Then O
perform O
the O
update O
joining O
to O
the O
temp O
table B-Library_Class
. O

That O
will O
ensure O
the O
lowest O
locking O
level O
and O
quickest O
access O
. O

You O
can O
also O
add O
an O
identity O
column B-Data_Structure

the O
temp O
table B-Library_Class
, O
than O
you O
can O

through O
and O
do O
the O
updates O
in O
batches O
. O

You O
set O
the O
header B-User_Interface_Element
to O
white-space O
: O
nowrap O
; O
therefore O
, O
the O
browser B-Application
is O
unable O
to O
break O
the O
headers B-User_Interface_Element
, O
so O
the O
width O
of O
the O
table B-User_Interface_Element
will O
be O
bigger O
than O
the O
container O
div O
. O

You O
can O
set O
, O
overflow O
: O
hidden O
; O
to O
cut O
the O
overflowing O
parts O
, O
or O
overflow O
: O
auto O
; O
to O
create O
a O

Both O
line O
feed O
( O

, O

) O
and O

return O
( O

, O

) O

; O

uses O

first O
, O
( O
old O
) O

latter O
, O

combination O
( O

) O
. O

If O

a O

library O
that O
abstracts O
this O
( O
and O
if O

absolutely O
have O
to O
support O
the O
old O
Mac B-Device
format O
( O
as O
the O
new O
MacOS B-Operating_System
, O
because O
the O
kernel B-Application
is O
Unix-based B-Operating_System
, O
also O
uses O
LF O
) O
) O
, O
treat O

and O

as O

separator O
, O
and O
do O

. O

. O

Second O

When O

. O

" O

" O

" O

for O

) O

This O
is O
a O
pretty O
obtuse O
answer O
, O
and O
definitely O
not O
a O
one-liner O
, O
but O
here O
is O
how O
it O
can O
be O
done O
in O
bash B-Programming_Language
, O
with O
a O
little O
help O
from O
bc O
and O
tr O
( O
works O
on O
osx B-Operating_System
) O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O
: O
A_2597 O
( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

This O
does O
the O
following O
; O

gets O
the O
length O
of O
the O
function O
name O

figures O
out O
number O
of O
case O
combinations O
( O
2^n O
) O

loops O
over O
each O
combination O

turns O
the O
combination O
number O
into O
a O
string B-Data_Type
of O
binary O
digits O

Fiddles O
the O
string B-Data_Type
of O
binary O
digits O
so O
it O
is O
the O
same O
length O
as O
the O
function O
name O

indexes O
through O
each O
char B-Data_Type
of O
the O
function O
name O
and O
string B-Data_Type
of O
binary O
digits O
and O
does O
a O
toupper() O
case O
change O
only O
if O
the O
corresponding O
binary O
digit O
is O
1 O

reassembles O
the O
chars B-Data_Type
to O
a O
string B-Data_Type

does O
a O
bash B-Programming_Language
alias O
from O
each O
combination O
to O
the O
function O
name O

Assumes O
the O
function O
is O
defined O
, O
and O
has O
an O
all-lowercase O
name O
. O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
20959651 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/20959651/ O


First O
I O
believe O
you O
mean O
D3 O
not O
A3 O
, O
since O
PWM O
does O
not O
exist O
on O
A3 O
. O

Assuming O
you O
are O
driving O
a O
DC B-Device
motor I-Device
, O
and O
not O
something O
like O
a O
servo B-Device
or O
stepper B-Device

You O
have O
two O
problems O
. O

1st O
. O

you O
may O
need O
a O
smoothing O
capacitor O
. O

Where O
your O
formula O
would O
be O
F O
= O
L*C O
Noting O
that O
analogWrite O
uses O
a O
F O
= O
490Hz O
. O

The O
concept O
is O
simple O
, O
in O
short O
the O
cap O
average O
out O
the O
high O
and O
lows O
of O
the O
PWM O
, O
based O
on O
the O
duty O
cycle O
. O

And O
the O
capacitance O
needed O
is O
based O
on O
the O
frequency O
and O
impedance O
. O

This O
will O
provide O
the O
analog O
voltage O
. O

2nd O
. O

And O
bigger O
problem O
is O
the O
output O
of O
the O
Arduino B-Device
can O
not O
supply O
sufficient O
current O
to O
drive O
the O
motor B-Device
correctly O
. O

It O
will O
max O
out O
at O
about O
20ma O
, O
and O
the O
motor B-Device
likely O
needs O
more O
. O

So O
at O
low O
speeds O
the O
pulses O
which O
were O
week O
, O
stall O
out O
during O
their O
low O
periods O
. O

You O
should O
have O
your O
PWM O
output O
drive O
a O
transistor B-Device
, O
which O
in O
turn O
will O
ON-OFF O
the O
motor B-Device
directly O
from O
the O
power O
supply O
. O

Now O
your O
motor O
may O
have O
enough O
inertia O
as O
not O
to O
need O
the O
cap O
. O

see O
adafruit-arduino-lesson-13-dc-motors/breadboard O
-layout O

and O
here O
for O
a O
discussion O
about O
the O
smoothing O
cap O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
10063672 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10063672/ O


You O
're O
loading O
a O
NIB O
that O
uses O
a O
10.7-specific O
feature O
, O
Cocoa O
Autolayout O
, O
on O
10.6 O
, O
which O
does O
n't O
understand O
it O
. O

If O
you O
wish O
to O
support O
running O
on O
10.6 O
, O
you O
need O
to O
avoid O
using O
such O
features O
. O

You O
should O
be O
able O
to O
set O
the O
deployment O
target O
on O
the O
NIB O

. O
. O

on O
your O

line I-Application

app O
: O

CODE_BLOCK O

( O
code O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

OK O
. O
Found O
an O
answer O
to O
one O
of O
the O
questions O
: O

The O
inline O
mootools B-Library
request O
did O
not O
execute O
when O
declared O
through O
the O
onclick() O
. O

It O
seems O

was O

by O
the O
script O
not O
being O
synchronous O
. O

So O
probably O
it O
returns O
without O
actually O
fully O
committing O
the O
request O
, O
and O
the O
browser B-Application
then O
moves O
to O
another O
page O
breaking O
the O
execution O
. O

Adding O
a O
synchronous O
call O
to O
the O
script O
fixes O
the O
problem O
: O

OP_BLOCK O
: O
( O
output O
omitted O
for O
annotation O
) O

problem O
that O

. O

However O
I O
am O

that O
to O
be O
as O
that O
was O
n't O
the O
main O
question O
raised O
. O

For O
trully O
offline-charts O
, O
there O
is O
a O
way O

While O
regular O
charts O
process O
an O
independent O
event-flow O
, O
received O
from O
MT4-Server B-Application
, O
there O
is O
a O
change O
for O
retaining O
your O
own O
control O
over O
TOHLCV-data O
records O
- O
- O
including O
the O
TimeZone O
shifts O
, O
synthetic O
Bar(s) O
additions O
and O
other O
adaptations O
, O
as O
needed O
. O

You O
may O
create O
your O
own O
, O
transformed O
, O
TOHLCV-history O
and O
import O
these O
records O
via O
F2 O
facility O
, O
called O
in O
MT4 B-Application
a O
History O
Centre O
. O

How O
to O
avoid O
a O
live-quote-stream O
updates O
in O
MetaTrader B-Application
Terminal I-Application
4 O

The O
simplest O
ever O
way O
is O
not O
to O
login O
to O
any O
Trading B-Application
Server I-Application
. O

This O
will O
avoid O
unwanted O
updates O
from O
reaching O
your O
local O
anFxQuoteStreamPROCESSOR O
. O

There O
used O
to O
be O
a O
way O
, O
how O
to O
inject O
fake O
QuoteStreamDATA O
into O
a O
local O
MT4 B-Application
, O
however O
this O
enters O
a O
gray O
, O
if O
not O
black O
zone O
, O
as O
MetaQuotes O
, O
Inc O
. O
, O
postulated O
the O
Server/Terminal B-Application
protocol O
to O
be O
a O
protected O
IP O
and O
any O
attempt O
to O
reverse-engineer O
they O
consider O
an O
unlawfull O
violation O
of O
their O
rights O
and O
could O
cause O
legal O
consequences O
, O
so O

carefull O

there O
. O

Anyway O
, O
a O
doable O

with O

risk O

being O
presented O
above O
. O

logback B-Library
is O
the O
default O
logging O
implementation O
used O
by O
Spring B-Library
Boot I-Library
( O

assume O
you O
are O

) O
. O

default O

shipped O
with O
Spring B-Library
which O

on O

, O
for O

spring B-Library

this O
is O

. O

If O

default O

and O

for O

. O

Not O

that O
you O
are O
probably O
doing O
to O
much O
and O

to O

. O

Below O
is O
the O
method O
to O
clone O
OpenCV B-Library
2.4.10 O
through O
TortoiseGit B-Application
2.4.0.3 O
. O

Clone O
OpenCV B-Library
HEAD O
from O
https://github.com/opencv/opencv.git O
. O

In O
the O
cloned O
directory O
, O
right O
click O
and O
select O
TortoiseGit B-Application
from O
the O
popup O
menu B-User_Interface_Element
. O

From O
the O
sub O
menu B-User_Interface_Element
, O
select O
Switch/Checkout O
. O

In O
Switch/Checkout O
menu B-User_Interface_Element
, O
select O
OpenCV-2.4.10 B-Library
from O
Branch O
or O
2.4.10 O
from O
Tag O
. O

See O
show O
log O
to O
verify O
if O
the O
right O
version O
is O
cloned O
or O
not O
. O

Hope O
this O
help O
. O

EDIT O
: O

The O
image B-User_Interface_Element
below O
shows O
the O
subfolder O
with O
the O
opencv-2.4.10 B-Library
core O
package O
from O
the O
GitHub B-Website
clone O
. O

of O

flawed O
and O
will O
break O
in O
unexpected O
ways O
in O
a O
multi-threading O
environment O
. O

The O

initialization O
of O

singleton B-Library_Class
, O

: O

( O
code O
omitted O
for O

) O

loader O
to O
handle O

, O

. O

does O

. O

: O

annotation O

: O

Do O
a O
regular O
expression O
find/replace O
like O
this O
: O

Open O
Replace O
Dialog B-User_Interface_Element

Find O
What O
: O
[ O
^ O
\[\]]*\[([^\]]+)\] O

Replace O
With O
: O
\1\n O

Check O
regular O
expression O

Click O
Replace O
or O
Replace O
All O

Explanation O

one O
problem O
is O
that O
brackets O
are O
RE O
metacharacters O
, O
that O
means O
we O
have O
to O
escape O
each O
bracket O
, O
when O
we O
need O
a O
literal O
bracket O
, O
i.e O
. O

a O
literal O
bracket O
becomes O
\ O
[ O
or O
\ O
] O
in O
the O
RE O

here O
in O
the O
RE O
we O
look O
for O
an O
optional O
part O
that O
may O
consist O
of O
everything O
not O
brackets O
( O
[ O
\ O
[ O
\ O
] O
] O
*) O

followed O
by O
an O
opening O
bracket O
, O
followed O
by O
somthing O
not O
a O
closing O
bracket O
(( O
[ O
^\ O
] O
] O
+)) O
which O
is O
also O
captured O
into O
\1 O
due O
to O
the O
parentheses O
, O
for O
reuse O
in O
the O
substitution O

whatever O
is O
matched O
above O
is O
completely O
replaced O
by O
whatever O
was O
captured O
into O
\1 O
followed O
by O
a O
newline O
( O
\n O
) O
, O
when O
you O
need O

, O

I O
'm O
not O
sure O
this O
would O
even O
work O
; O
if O
, O
say O
, O
the O
person O
reference O
was O
null O
, O
what O
would O
the O
runtime O
replace O
it O
with O
? O

A O
new O
Person O
? O

That O
would O
require O
the O
Person O
to O
have O
some O
default O
initialization O
that O
you O
'd O
expect O
in O
this O
case O
. O

You O
may O
avoid O
null O
reference O
exceptions O
but O
you O
'd O
still O
get O
unpredictable O
behavior O
if O
you O
did O
n't O
plan O
for O
these O
types O
of O
setups O
. O

The O
? O
? O

operator O
in O
C# B-Programming_Language
might O
be O
best O
termed O
the O
" O
coalesce O
" O
operator O
; O
you O
can O
chain O
several O
expressions O
and O

will O
return O

NotificationCenter B-Library_Class
and O
using O
Closures O
to O
communicate O
between O
two O
instances O
? O

they O

, O

should O
I O

? O

, O

- O

class O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
41944911 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41944911/ O


In O
some O
cases O
the O
patterns O
are O
interchangeable O
, O
however O
: O

Using O
a O
closure O
is O
the O
simplest O
solution O
for O
simple O
cases O

Using O
a O
delegate O
is O
common O
when O
there O
is O
complex O
communication O
between O
two O
objects O
. O

One O
delegate O
can O
be O
better O
than O
many O
closures O
. O

You O
have O
to O
use O
notifications O
when O
you O
have O
multiple O
observers O
or O
when O
you O
are O
not O
sure O
what O
objects O
will O
be O
observing O
. O

You O
might O
be O
asking O
yourself O
why O
we O
are O
using O
closures O
for O
simple O
cases O
and O
not O
delegates O
or O
notifications O
. O

The O
answer O
is O
that O
closures O
are O
the O
most O
lightweight O
. O

They O
are O
easy O
to O
create O
and O
they O
positively O
affect O
your O
code O
quality O
. O

Let O
's O
consider O
a O
completion O
callback O
. O

If O
you O
decide O
to O
use O
a O
notification O
, O
you O
need O
another O
method O
that O
will O
handle O
that O
notification O
. O

The O
same O
is O
valid O
for O
delegates O
. O

If O
you O
need O
some O
context O
( O
e.g O
. O
the O
parameters O
that O
triggered O
the O
actions O
) O
, O
you O
will O
need O
to O
save O
it O
into O
a O
property O
. O

On O
the O
other O
hand O
, O
a O
closure O
can O
be O
created O
inline O
. O

That O
means O
that O
the O
code O
that O
triggers O
the O
action O
and O
handles O
its O
result O
is O
at O
one O
place O
. O

This O
really O
simplifies O
the O
structure O
of O
your O
code O
. O

Also O
note O
that O
if O
the O
closure O
needs O
some O
context O
, O
it O
can O
capture O
it O
, O
without O
the O
need O
to O
create O
an O
additional O
property O
. O

between O

. O

- O

some O

, O

set O

, O

. O

. O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
46419176 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/46419176/ O


As O
long O
as O
there O
is O
an O
owner O
relation O
between O
two O
windows B-User_Interface_Element
. O

the O
owner O
of O
a O
window B-User_Interface_Element
can O
never O
be O
on O
top O
of O
the O
owned O
window B-User_Interface_Element
. O

Windows B-User_Interface_Element
in O
an O
owner O
, O
parent O
, O
child O
relation O
always O
behave O
the O
same O
. O

The O
owned/child O
window B-User_Interface_Element
is O
always O
on O
top O
of O
the O
parent/owner O
. O

If O
you O
want O
to O
break O
this O
, O
you O
have O
to O
break O
the O
owner/child O
relation O
. O

Let O
all O
dialog B-User_Interface_Element
windows I-User_Interface_Element
have O
no O
owner O
.. O
. O
than O
they O
may O
float O
freely O
. O

But O
: O
I O
will O
expect O
the O
you O
program O
does O
n't O
behave O
better O
. O

Even O
worse O
. O

User O
might O
search O
windows B-User_Interface_Element
that O
are O
deep O
below O
covered O
under O
other O
windows B-User_Interface_Element
. O

And O
they O
will O
never O
get O
in O
front O
, O
when O
your O
program O
gets O
active O
. O

See O
the O
description O
about O
parent/child/owned O
windows B-User_Interface_Element
here O
. O

Also O
this O
article O
might O
be O
helpful O
. O

Edit O
: O
The O
problem O
is O
that O
internally O
the O
MFC B-Library
sets O
the O
main O
window B-User_Interface_Element
as O
an O
owner O
if O
no O
parent O
is O
given O
. O

Only O
the O
call O
to O
BOOL O
Wnd O
:: O
CreateDlgIndirect(LPCDLGTEMPLATE O
lpDialogTemplate O
, O
CWnd O
* O
pParentWnd O
, O
HINSTANCE O
hInst O
) O
allows O
to O
leave O
pParentWnd O
NULL O
. O

So O
you O
may O
create O
the O
window B-User_Interface_Element
as O
normal O
, O
but O
use O
SetParent(NULL) O
after O
it O
was O
created O
. O

Again O
the O
MFC B-Library
ASSERTs O
this O
. O

SO O
you O
may O
use O
the O
API B-Library
function O
and O
the O
handle O
of O
your O
dialog B-Library_Class
. O

EDIT O
: O

IIUC O
, O
you O
have O
a O
similarity O
formula O
per O
field O
, O
and O
you O
want O
to O
use O
it O
per O
document O
, O
running O
against O
all O
other O
documents O
. O

You O
can O
use O
several O
options O
, O
all O
at O
indexing O
time O
: O

Extend O
the O
DefaultSimilarity B-Library_Class
class O
. O

Extend O
the O
SimilarityDelegator B-Library_Class
class O
, O
if O
you O
only O
need O
to O
modify O
part O
of O
the O
methods O
. O

In O
both O
methods O
, O
you O
may O
make O
use O
of O
payloads O
to O
store O
term-specific O
information O
( O
could O
be O
useful O
for O
the O
lat-long O
data O
) O
. O

After O
implementing O
a O
Similarity B-Library_Class
class O
using O
one O
of O
these O
methods O
, O
use O
Similarity.setDefault(mySimilarity) O
to O
set O
this O
as O
the O
Similarity B-Library_Class
instance O
for O
indexing O
and O
searching O
. O

Only O
then O
index O
your O
text O
corpus O
, O
which O
you O
can O
search O
later O
- O
you O
will O
probably O
have O
to O
extend O
the O
Searcher B-Library_Class
class O
as O
well O
to O
get O
the O
raw O
similarity O
. O

Having O
said O
that O
, O
I O
believe O
this O
approach O
is O
wrong O
for O
your O
use O
case O
- O
Lucene B-Library
is O
optimized O
to O
get O
a O
few O
similar O
documents O
, O
not O
a O
score O
for O
every O
one O
, O
so O
I O
predict O
the O
runtime O
will O
be O
prohibitive O
- O
Hope O
I O
am O
wrong O
, O
but O
nevertheless O
I O
suggest O
you O
read O
Mining O
of O
Massive O
Datasets O
for O
a O
better O
approach O
- O
min O
hashes O
and O
shingling O
. O

Good O
luck O
. O

Patrick O
, O
I O
will O
first O
quote O
Grant O
Ingersoll O
about O
modifying O
the O
Similarity B-Library_Class
class O
: O
" O
Here O
be O
Dragons O
" O
. O

Customizing O

's O
Similarity I-Library_Class
class O
is O
hard O
. O

I O
have O
done O
this O
. O

It O
is O
not O

. O

Only O
do O

if O

absolutely O

. O

I O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
14076772 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/14076772/ O


Typically O
the O
Memento O
pattern O
is O
used O
to O
implement O
roll-back/save O
point O
support O
. O

For O
example O
I O
might O
want O
to O
mark O
the O
state O
of O
an O
object O
at O
a O
point O
in O
time O
, O
do O
some O
work O
and O
then O
decide O
to O
revert O
that O
object O
back O
to O
the O
point O
at O
which O
is O
was O
marked O
. O

The O
implementation O
of O
a O
Memento O
pattern O
could O
use O
serialisation O
, O
which O
would O
involve O
saving O
the O
contents O
of O
the O
object O
into O
a O
byte[] B-Data_Structure
and O
keeping O
in O
memory O
or O
writing O
to O
disk B-Device
. O

When O
reverting O
the O
content O
of O
the O
object O
would O
be O
rebuilt O
from O
the O
serialised O
copy O
. O

Conversely O
I O
could O
implement O
a O
Memento O
pattern O
by O
cloning O
the O
object O
in O
memory O
and O
keeping O
a O
reference O
to O
the O
copy O
and O
then O
copying O
the O
state O
back O
if O
the O
object O
needs O
reverting O
. O

This O
method O
does O
n't O
use O
serialisation O
. O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
14076772 O

Question_URL O
: O
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/14076772/ O


The O
Memento O
pattern O
is O
an O
OO O
design O
pattern O
used O
to O
keep O
previous O
states O
of O
an O
object O
in O
memory O
. O

It O
's O
useful O
to O
implement O
an O
" O
Undo O
" O
operation O
, O
for O
example O
. O

Serialization O
is O
the O
process O
of O
transforming O
a O
graph B-Data_Structure
of O
objects O
to O
a O
byte B-Data_Structure
array I-Data_Structure
, O
in O
order O
to O
save O
it O
on O
disk B-Device
, O
or O
send O
it O
to O
another O
JVM B-Application
over O
the O
network O
, O
for O
example O
. O

They O
do O
n't O
have O
much O
in O
common O
. O

Answer_to_Question_ID O
: O
16350473 O

Question_URL O
